                <h1>Effective Ways to Remove Wallpaper Glue from Walls</h1>
                <p>To clean wallpaper glue off walls, start by scraping off excess glue with a putty knife. Then, mix warm water and a few drops of dish soap in a bucket. Soak a sponge in the solution and gently scrub the affected area. Rinse with clean water and wipe dry with a cloth. Repeat if necessary for stubborn spots.</p>
